headline: PG&E Decreases Residential Electric Rates on Sept. 1; Customers Receive California Climate Credit on October Electric Bills
summary: Electric rates for all Pacific Gas and Electric Company (PG&E) residential customers decreased by 2.1% on September 1. For the typical residential customer who uses 500 kilowatt hours a month and does not receive discounts, monthly bills will decrease by about $5.
